CD38


Description

ADP-ribosyl cyclase/cyclic ADP-ribose hydrolase 1 (CD38). Synthesizes the second messengers cyclic ADP-ribose and nicotinate-adenine dinucleotide phosphate, the former a second messenger for glucose-induced insulin secretion. Also has cADPr hydrolase activity. Also moonlights as a receptor in cells of the immune system.


Clinical trials

NCT03638206 - Colorectal Cancer, Esophagus Cancer, Renal Carcinoma, Hepatoma, Lung Cancer, Mesothelioma, Ovarian Cancer, Pancreatic Cancer, Melanoma
